  <summary>5/7/1987--Introduced.
Consumer Protection Act of 1987 - Prohibits any person from offering the sale at a discount rate of services using a nationwide system of reservation which requires the services to be used at a particular time and date, unless information regarding the availability of such services is disclosed.</summary>
